  "instructions": [
    "preheat the oven to 375°f (190°c).",
    "roll out the dough to a thickness of 1/8 inch (3 mm).",
    "transfer the dough to a 9-inch (23 cm) tart pan with a removable bottom.",
    "trim the edges and press the dough into the corners of the pan.",
    "in a medium bowl, whisk together the granulated sugar, apricot jam, yuzu juice, and yuzu zest.",
    "arrange the fresh apricots on top of the dough, leaving a 1-inch (2.5 cm) border around the edges.",
    "brush the edges of the dough with the egg wash.",
    "sprinkle the confectioners' sugar evenly over the apricots.",
    "bake the tart for 40-45 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the apricots are tender.",
    "allow the tart to cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes before serving."
  ],
